# =============================================================================
# CLAUDE.local.md Example
# =============================================================================
# LOCATION: <project-root>/CLAUDE.local.md  (NOT committed to git)
#
# PURPOSE:  Personal overrides that only apply to YOU. This file is gitignored
#           so it won't affect your teammates.
#
# USE CASES:
#   - You prefer a different editor than the team default
#   - You want extra verbose output during development
#   - You have local paths that differ from the team standard
#   - You want to temporarily disable a rule
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Copy this file to your project's root directory
#   2. Rename it to CLAUDE.local.md
#   3. Add your personal overrides
#   4. Make sure .gitignore includes CLAUDE.local.md
# =============================================================================

# Personal Overrides

## My Preferences
# Add any personal rules that override the project CLAUDE.md.
# These only apply to your machine.

# Example: I prefer verbose output during development
# - Always show full stack traces in error messages
# - Include debug logging in test runs

# Example: My local paths differ from the team
# - My database runs on port 5433 (not the default 5432)
# - My Redis instance is at localhost:6380

# Example: Temporary overrides
# - Skip linting on save (I'll run it manually)
# - Use draft mode for all builds (faster iteration)
